<title>JAPAN: Konami shares weakened by competition worries.</title>
<headline>Konami shares weakened by competition worries.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-01-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in Konami Co Ltd were down in Wednesday afternoon trade, enfeebled by worries that the video game software firm will be left behing by its competitors, brokers said.</p>
<p>At 0500 GMT, the shares were down 170 yen at 3,180 yen.  </p>
<p>&quot;Its competitors are trying to find new distribution routes, selling at places like convenience stores,&quot; said a trader at a second-tier brokerage. &quot;But Konami is sticking to mail-order sales.&quot;</p>
</text>
